## 2. Profile Overview

This profile applies to Token Exchange requests of the form:

```
POST /token HTTP/1.1
Host: as.example.com
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded
<client authentication per AS policy>

grant_type=urn%3Aietf%3Aparams%3Aoauth%3Agrant-type%3Atoken-exchange
&subject_token=<JWT representing the Principal>
&subject_token_type=urn%3Aietf%3Aparams%3Aoauth%3Atoken-type%3Ajwt
&actor_token=<JWT representing the agent — this profile applies here>
&actor_token_type=urn%3Aietf%3Aparams%3Aoauth%3Atoken-type%3Ajwt
&audience=<target resource server>
```

The profile defines, for the `actor_token` JWT:

```
+-------+--------------------------------------------------------+
| Claim | Purpose                                                |
+-------+--------------------------------------------------------+
| aid   | Name of a profile in the agent operator's metadata.    |
|       | The named profile MAY carry an entitlement constraint  |
|       | or MAY be entitlement-free. Mutually exclusive with    |
|       | ent.                                                   |
| ent   | Inline entitlement; a JSON object validated against    |
|       | the agent operator's declared profiles. Mutually       |
|       | exclusive with aid.                                    |
+-------+--------------------------------------------------------+
```

Plus, for the agent operator’s OAuth client metadata, one member:

```
+----------------------+-----------------------------------------+
| Member               | Purpose                                 |
+----------------------+-----------------------------------------+
| entitlement_profiles | Object declaring named profiles agents  |
|                      | of this operator may reference. A       |
|                      | profile may be entitlement-free.        |
+----------------------+-----------------------------------------+
```

Both actor_token claims are OPTIONAL. An actor_token carrying neither is a conformant [RFC8693] actor_token outside the scope of this profile.

The AS processes a profile-conformant Token Exchange as follows:

1. Validate the actor_token per [RFC8693] Section 2.1 (signature against the agent operator’s keys, `iss`, `aud`, `exp`, etc.).
1. If both `aid` and `ent` are present, reject (Section 5.4).
1. If `aid` is present, resolve it against the agent operator’s `entitlement_profiles` metadata; the named profile may or may not carry an entitlement constraint (Section 4.3.2).
1. If `ent` is present, check it is well-formed and validate it against the agent operator’s declared profiles (Section 4.3.3).
1. Apply local policy. Issue a token. Optionally reflect agent identity and entitlement into the issued token’s `act` claim (Section 5.3).

